REMARK 280                                                                      
REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: SARS-COV-2 MPRO WAS THAWED AND DILUTED   
REMARK 280  TO 6 MG/ML (USING 20 MM HEPES, PH 7.5, 50 MM NACL). BETA-LACTAM     
REMARK 280  20E WAS ADDED TO THE PROTEIN SOLUTION TO A FINAL CONCENTRATION      
REMARK 280  OF 10 MM; THE MIXTURE WAS INCUBATED FOR 2 H AT AMBIENT              
REMARK 280  TEMPERATURE PRIOR TO DISPENSING PLATES. THE DROP COMPOSITION WAS    
REMARK 280  0.15 UL PROTEIN LIGAND SOLUTION, 0.3 UL 11 PERCENT V/V PEG 4000,    
REMARK 280  0.1 M MES, PH 6.5, AND 0.05 ,MICROL MPRO CRYSTAL SEED STOCK. THE    
REMARK 280  MPRO CRYSTAL SEED STOCK WAS PREPARED BY CRUSHING MPRO CRYSTALS      
REMARK 280  WITH A PIPETTE TIP, SUSPENDING THEM IN 30% PEG 4000, 5%V/V DMSO,    
REMARK 280  0.1 M MES PH 6.5, AND VORTEXING FOR 60 S WITH APPROXIMATELY 10      
REMARK 280  GLASS BEADS (1.0 MM DIAMETER, BIOSPEC PRODUCTS). AS RESERVOIR       
REMARK 280  SOLUTION WAS USED: 11%V/V PEG 4K, 5%V/V DMSO, 0.1 M MES, PH 6.5.    
REMARK 280  CRYSTALS WERE GROWN USING THE SITTING DROP VAPOR DIFFUSION          
REMARK 280  METHOD AT 20 DEGREE C AND APPEARED WITHIN 24 H, REACHING FULL       
REMARK 280  SIZE WITHIN 36 H. CRYSTALS WERE LOOPED AFTER ONE WEEK., VAPOR       
REMARK 280  DIFFUSION, SITTING DROP, TEMPERATURE 293K                           
